wikipedia_page.main: Jane Procter (2 November 1810 – 5 January 1882) was a British headmistress, suffragist and temperance campaigner. She founded what would become the Quaker Polam Hall School in Darlington.

response: 'Polam Hall' was sold to William and Robert Thompson, who leased it to the Procter sisters for use as a Quaker ladies’ finishing school. Jane Proctor had founded her first school in Selby which had lasted for twenty years. She founded "Selby School" in 1848 as a boarding school for girls at Number 11 Townhouse, in Houndgate helped by her sisters Elizabeth and Barbara. Their school moved to Polam Hall after six years with Jane Procter as the head.
